<br>
I play a 47 warrior, and I feel that we are headed down the same path as the wizard.<br>
<br>
In a normal exp group, there just isn't need for us. There are other classes that do what we do. .  and then some.<br>
<br>
When it comes to a raid? Our extra hp/ac does prove to be the best choice as the main tank. <br>
<br>
The same is true for the wizard. We are almost useless in a group. (I'll save you my wizard rant) We do massive amounts of damage in a short period of time. It's unfortunate, but we can not hold this massive DPS for a long period of time. Which makes us perfect for a raid encounter, and underpowered for a normal exp group.<br>
<br>
The difference I see? Wizards can quad kite, warrior's can NOT solo over a long period of time unless:<br>
<br>
A.) They have a fungi and some very nice weapons.<br>
B.) They have a 2nd box running another class.<br>
<br>
What does this mean in my opinion?<br>
<br>
Eventually, as other classes become more used in place of warriors, we won't be needed in normal exp groups. What does this mean? We're stuck with the same options as the wizard has for grouping: AE groups or your own group of friends. Soon, I forsee pick up groups not being a thing a warrior gets.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cents on the issue. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usasraaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sasraaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/7/02 7:53:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=84>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The State of Warriors in EQ</span><hr size=1> I'll start by saying that I do think Warriors have some big complains, one if which is taunt and agro.  There were a lot of good points in this thread, a lot that I didn't even know about.  I play a 59 sk, who started playing the first day of Kunark, currently in a guild that is starting to move out of HoT.  However I do disagree or have a different view of some of the problems list.<br>
<br>
For the longest time, Warriors have been the only class that can fill the MT role, whether in exp groups or on raids.  I remember having to beg my cleric friend to get me into groups because it was so bad.  I often solo'd, not because I wanted to, but because I didn't want to wait hours for a group to settle for me, and then break up a few minutes after, so I very much understand where some people are coming from.  <br>
<br>
But I think its a good thing that other classes are now able to fill the MT roles in different instances.  Before Tank = Warrior; I remember joining my guild, and someone asking for a tank to join an exp group, I asked if I could join and they simply laughed at me.  Now though Tanks = warrior, sk, pally, monk, ranger, occasional pet, which is on par with the other roles in the game.<br>
<br>
Yet Warriors have not lost their role in the game.  I still can not come close to a warriors DPS, and I don't believe that most sk's/pally's can, at least not until the end game that the majority will not play.  In fact I don't believe Rangers start to until higher levels and until they get a ton of AA skills, though I don't know this for sure.  Warriors still have far more HP's than sk's/pally's do.  Warriors can tank mobs that hit harder than 400 pts, in which case I would be hesitant to tank other than to stop ping ponging.  Granted higher level SK's and Pally's with much better gear than mine and AA skills probably can tank those mobs, but sitting at 2450 hp unbuffed, I&quot;m sure not going to try it.<br>
<br>
As for desirability, in exp groups you may see a ton of warriors LFG compared to sk's/pally's, but that is probably because the shear difference in number of people playing warriors compared to sk/pally's.  Also, if you look at a lot of guild rosters, you will see easily 10 warriors per guild, but probably around 1-3 sk's.  I know 3 of the top guild on my server have one sk per guild, and deem that enough for the guild.  <br>
<br>
As for AA skills, I think a lot of people have complaints.  The monk rapid feign, which was mentioned before. is supposedly causing a lot of failed feigns.  Some of the Mage pet skills don't work at all I have also been told.  As for sk's, please don't think of the unholy steed as more than a toy.  Sure it is fast, but I'd gladly trade it for an actual offensive discipline or a skill that will allow me to cause a little bit of melee damage.  Not to mention that its not that practical when you can consider you can get run 3 at lv 51 or Jboots at anytime. Then we have a bunch of skills that focus on HT, argueable one of the most worthless skills on a raid, resisted by most higher level mobs.  For the Rangers and Pally's, they have to get lv 59 and get 30+ aa pts just to become sort of effective on a raid, in terms of melee/bow damage.<br>
<br>
In conclusion, you guys have some serious issues, but I don't believe the class is in as bad a shape as you think it is.  Warriors still have a role in the game, one that will never be taken away, whether by offensive upgrades or aa points.<br>
<br>
Sasraaz<br>
59th lv Revenant of Greenmist<br>
Lizzard of Infusion<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukraydak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kraydak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/7/02 12:38:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=85>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The State of Warriors in EQ</span><hr size=1> I think there is an issue which people have been avoiding or skirting the edges of.<br>
<br>
There is an AC soft cap (around 1200-1300 for warriors).  Warriors tend to hit this cap first of all the classes but all melee classes hit it eventually.<br>
<br>
There is a resist soft cap (around 150-180 for lvl 60s).  I imagine casters tend to hit this one first, but everyone does eventually.<br>
<br>
The biggy: there is an hp softcap (I'd estimate around 6k).  To see this, take the CH rotation your guild can produce, and check if you have the hp to tank the mob you want to.  If you can, more hp are superfluous.  I'm in a HoT guild, so can only guess at what this cap is at the true endgame, but my guess is above.  Knights can reach this, in fact, I think all melee classes can reach it.  Warriors certainly hit it first, but once others have achieved it, the order of achievement matters not at all.<br>
<br>
To look at it another way, the hp advantage warriors have over knights at 60 (with 255 sta) is around 400hp (I'm not going to check on Magelo).  This is less than a *third* of a bubble of health for Furor.  If Verant tries to make an encounter which needs a warrior (without worrying about defensive) *that* is the amount of leeway they have.  In other words, not enough.<br>
<br>
So, with the current EQ set up (straight hp adders give the same, no matter the class/level) the only advantage uber warriors have is defensive/evasive.  So to design an encounter that needs a warrior to tank you'd have to make a mob that can *single round kill anyone* without defensive up.  Say a mob that quads with a DB of 0, and a DI of 125 (so max hit of 2500, 1250 with defensive).  IE, warriors are screwed, and there is little Verant can do to change this without some serious overhauls.<br>
<br>
As a sudden thought, mobs that have a staight hp debuff effect of some kind on the order of several k hp would work too (the natural hp advantage warriors have is more important the fewer hp people have in general, which is why non-uber guilds don't see the problem).<br>
<br>
-Kraydak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufurorplanedefiler.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Furor Planedefiler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/7/02 3:48:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=86>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  That is correct..</span><hr size=1> And another reason why I NEVER EVER allow the argument of HPs = Mitigation.<br>
