Work up your ATK values and HPs, though, as nothing else matters.<br>
<br>
This game is broken <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uthegrudgebearer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Grudgebearer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/02 5:57:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=87>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The State of Warriors in EQ</span><hr size=1> A few things:-<br>
<br>
Since the release of Kunark and Defensive, I knew that our class would eventually turn into one of those &quot;one hit wonder&quot; classes where if we ever ask for something down the road we will get told &quot;But you have defensive&quot;. I agree with lots that defensive, while arguably still our greatest skill, might be the very skill that comes back to bite us in the ass.  I am too noticing it.<br>
<br>
Verant also never upgrades classes properly. Take Rangers for example. The Ranger community complained about the obvious problems for months and months. Verant threw them about 200 bones to shut them up. And by the time they finally did what they were supposed to do and correctly balanced them they become too powerful.  All these half assed balances followed by correct balances on top of it has caused a huge influx of mellee into the game (especially monks on Fennin).<br>
<br>
 80% of of 59+ rangers will tank over me in exp groups at 56 (they have nearly identical ac and hp, but better level, maybe my equip is really bad heh not 100% sure. around 1050ac, 2500hp). A pet can outtank me at this level (BST and Mage).  Now while I am sure 60 is great for warriors, 51-56 has been otherwise for me.  I have had  a very hard time finding groups. I cannot taunt any mobs even or higher than me, something your local  SK and Paladin or similar level can do with casting spells. And taunting off monks, rangers and rogues who all seem to have their epics when my epic is a long ways away is hard. <br>
<br>
The one benefit is the people who are willing to grind it out will be the ones left and deserving of the title &quot;Warlord&quot;. The downside is anyone who has the cash/equip or guild backing can make it easily anyways if they want to.<br>
<br>
I won't even mention the overpopulation of very well equiped twinked warriors on high population servers to contend with because their main is bored (again see infulx of mellees). I think everyone wants to be a warrior deep down, hence why it is such a populated class in Everquest.<br>
<br>
<br>
I have also noticed a few jabs coming at warriors in exp groups lately. Like Furor said they are snickering about it because they know just how good they have it now. Even Rangers pass comments these days to me about warriors in general (taunt and getting hit), I never thought I would see the day when that would happen. Lots of people of my lvl, but different class have better ac than me now.&quot;.  I wish I could buy a 35ac cloak for 10kpp or get one as easily.   Its all come down to the one hit wonder &quot;defensive&quot;.<br>
<br>
I too think about why I choose this class sometimes when Bob the paladin next to me can get Kunark and some other armor way easier than me, has an incredible healing spell at 59 and a 90% res. He can out-solo me, out-taunt me and I will have to do twice the work to get my equivalent armor to him. I am not going to be MTing for my guild anytime soon, nor do we do stuff where multiple lvl 60 defensive tanks are needed. I guess I will plod along until I reach the gold at the end of the rainbow that is &quot;lvl 60&quot; and see for myself.  Its gonna take a lot of work...<br>
<br>
But there is just something about the warrior class that keeps me coming back <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  well that and I will never ever  level another character again past 50, xp is just too ridiculous. I guess you stay with what you got and like someone else said here &quot;suck it up&quot; or quit. Some changes are needed though IMO. I do love my class, and there are lots of good points to it, but this post is not really about that. And I agree a bit of roughing it has helped me and will help me in the long run (I played since release anyways so I know what its like), but it does get me down sometimes when I just seem to not be needed, I chose this class for that very reason.<br>
<br>
On the flip side, ironically I am kinda glad in some ways our AA is not that great. It means less timesinks on tedious xping for skills I really do not need. <br>
<br>
I like the defensive table idea myself.<br>
<br>
Lastly:- Necros and Mages can have a spot in my group any day, two of the most undervalued classes in all of EQ IMO, specially Necros. They rock. I will also take a cleric over a shaman any day in exp groups if their role is to heal, I have never seen the opposite. If a slower is needed, well thats a different story <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <br>
<br>
Just a point of view from a random drunken rambling 56 warrior in his experiences in EQ.<br>
<br>
