My point of this whole thread is that hybrids should NOT get the exact same point increase, period, it should be unreachable, a level which makes you say &quot;Gee, it's a damn good thing I have all this other stuff cause if it were just melee, he would be DRASTICALLY better than me.&quot;<br>
<br>
The whole point here is that warriors should be FAR above all others in the area of absorbing damage.   Not a little, a LOT.  This is the whole point.   Warriors, by virtue of the fact that they have NOTHING else except them and their equipment should ALWAYS be FAR superior to non specific melee in defense, and still somewhat superior in terms of offense with the exception of monks and rogues and perhaps rangers with arrows.  We should have BETTER weapons, which we do not, we should have BETTER armor which we do not.<br>
<br>
The sad fact is that even if the AC softcap were lifted, it wouldn't do any thing to help warriors, because out of the multiple armor slots available, almost every &quot;top&quot; AC item goes to other than warriors, again, this would give monks the biggest advantage, and I'd say warriors the weakest.  Most people probably don't pay attention to equipment, particularly AC since it doesn't really matter, but there is almost NOTHING beyond Velious quest armor where warriors have the AC edge on ANY piece of equipment.<br>
