<br>
AA shouldn't CLOSE THE GAP between warriors and hybrids.  If they both max their tanking AA, Warriors should still be X% ahead of the hybrids, which should be exactly X% that they were before AA.  Any other reasoning is just spin doctor PR BS to cover the fact that they screwed up.<br>
<br>
2nd, we're not talking about paladin's offense.  We're talking about Defense here.  I group with a 59 monk, and granted he has been in one of the uberguilds on the server for a couple months, and I'm not, so he has a couple nice pieces of gear (25 ac neck, 40 ac tunic, dain crown, 25ac boots).  My warrior is wearing champs BP, and Fierce Heraldic in the other slots.  His AC is about 80 or 100 points behind mine, and he has about 1k less hp.<br>
<br>
He accidently pulled 2 mobs in CT last nite, both the same type, so we each ended up tanking one.  After both mobs were slowed, WHY IN THE HELL does the monk tank better than me? Why?  His red bar was moving slower than mine was.  He has no AA.  I have CA2 and CS 1, regen 3,  200 more HP per bubble of health, and 100 more ac, and yet he takes less damage than me.  You tell me in what fantasy world you're living in where that is balanced.  I can't even come close to his damage output, (which I give up to be able to tank better) and yet he tanks better than me, with 20 less AA and less AC/Hp.<br>
<br>
The classes should be balanced with give and take...there is a whole lot of taking going on for a lot of classes, but they ain't giving anything anymore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufrodlin7th.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Frodlin7th</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/02 2:28:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=98>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Blah!</span><hr size=1> ------------------------------------------------------<br>
First Slay undead is very situational. it's just an eyecandy.<br>
------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
It's not eye candy when you can go to the Grey and whip up a bunch of aa points with almost no downtime.  It's situational in that you actually have to go to where the undead are to solo with ease, but it's still highly powerful.  To minimize it's efictiveness by saying that it's &quot;eye candy&quot; is utter nonsense, there IS indeed a gameplay issue here.  Fine, it's not extreme against high end mobs, this doesn't make it irrelevant.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
_______________________________________________<br>
Paladins Offense and Melee skill caps is 225.<br>
Paladins have less hp than warriors.<br>
Paladins parry/dodge/riposte is way lower than warriors.<br>
Paladins have no disciplines.<br>
_______________________________________________<br>
<br>
You don't have dual wield either, or any other catch phrase that's 3 years old but what has been done to compensate for this?<br>
<br>
1. Paladins have 220HP more by adding Brell's.  In a regular exp group this cannot be overlooked if a Paladin is replacing a warrior, the only place where it balances out is on raids where both toons are buffed with it.<br>
<br>
2. You have HELLISHLY better weapons than warriors, which indeed compensate for any weapons skill cap difference, or dual wield difference.<br>
<br>
3. Your defense skill is identical to that of warriors, yet you are correct in saying that the avoidance skills are lower.  Can I enlighten you for a minute? <br>
<br>
I riposte in one day approximately 4.6%, Dodge 3.81% and Parry 5.63% of all blows.   Let's look at that closely shall we?<br>
<br>
If we took the SAME rolls, and compensated for the difference in skills, you would Riposte 4.2%, Dodge 3.6% and parry 5.2% of all blows.  In other words, it's absolutely meaningless UNLESS the parry occurred at a final blow which killed the toon, which, by nature of your laying of hands would very likely be prevented in the first place.   The notion that the difference in the avoidance skills, which is miniscule, is enough to compensate for all of your inherent advantages is nonsense.   Warriors should be a LOT better melee damage takers, not just a little.<br>
<br>
_______________________________________________<br>
Paladins have just a bit better Taunt because of the spells.<br>
_______________________________________________<br>
<br>
Yes, and rogues have just a bit better melee damage output than mages because of backstab.   Stun is an amazingly reliable taunt.  How do I know this?  Well, I did something funny one day....<br>
<br>
<br>
I said to myself &quot;Self, let's test a couple of things.   First, let's see about Luclin mobs and their inherent AC issues.  Second, let's see how well stun works as an aggro generator.&quot;<br>
<br>
So, I run down to Splitpaw, kill a few doggies, and wind up snaggin a couple of gnoll hide lariats.   My pet owning buddies tell me that they need em.   So.......wasnt' too long after that that I hear that good ol Rhag 1 is up, and needing some GRC copies, we're gonna go off him, but I couldn't get to Ssra in time for Rhag one, as it doesnt' take a whole lot to kill him.   Oh well, no biggie, I get there in time for Rhag 2 though.  <br>
<br>
Being the MT for my guild, I got to be in the position to tank good ol Modzeh, but today I decided to do something a tad different.   I wielded, instead of my standard weapons (11/17 and 13/20), I wielded my new uber Gnoll Hide Lariats (3/20).   Turns out, those things were a proc powerhouse, and I've never held aggro as easily.  So Easy, I didn't have to taunt to keep aggro.  Sadly, after parsing my damage, I learned that with gnoll hide lariats I came VERY close to the same damage as I did with my regular weapons set.<br>
<br>
THe lesson opened my eyes twofold:<br>
<br>
1. Stun is an INSANE aggro generator, to the point where I didn't even have to taunt to keep aggro<br>
<br>
2. n00b weapons that get put on pets are every bit as useful on Ssra mobs as non-enraging blow difficult to acquire weapons.<br>
<br>
<br>
______________________________________________<br>
Beldukill has explained why warrior don't get Physical Enhancement and Absor did it some time ago on EQ board also ( boards.station.sony.com/u...00583.html )<br>
______________________________________________<br>
<br>
Why would you quote VI to dismiss an argument that VI has screwed up on balancing melee?   They screwed up by giving that skill to Paladins and SK's and not warriors, as it thins the line between pure melee and Knights.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
_____________________________________________________________________<br>
Quote:<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 By this, I mean that the rate of VI limited Pal/SK only equipment, particularly in Luclin is fairly dramatic <br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I don't know what are u talking about. All Luclin PAL/SK weapons are worse than Velious ones ( except goldenrod ) <br>
Warriors Luclin's 1handers are HUGE upgrades from velious and there are a lot of em !<br>
<br>
for other gear..hum the only pal/sk item i could think is emperor shield.<br>
______________________________________________________________________<br>
<br>
You must have missed where I specifically stated that the upgrades that I was referring to were armor upgrades, and not weapons, but I'll play along anyway.<br>
<br>
How much of an upgrade is there between a BoC and Hategiver?  HUGE?  Hell no, it's a dwongrade.  Bloodfrenzy?  HUGE?  Hell no, it's a little nicer, but not much.<br>
<br>
Although, if you can show me an equivalent warrior helm to the THO helm is on a mob as easy, I'm all ears.  If you can show me where a warrior can pick up a semi-exclusive (i.e. warrior + 1 other class) upgrade to their back slot that's 35AC with a single group I'd be interested in seeing it.   Show me the limited access post-Velious quest armor stuff for warriors, and get off the &quot;our overpowered weapons from Velious weren't upgraded in Luclin&quot; horse, cause it doesn't fly.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ulorddaeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lorddaeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/02 3:09:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=99>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: warriors need help</span><hr size=1> i don't know how to pull quotes yet. so please excuse the copy' and pastes please.<br>
<br>
but the infamous Brutul said &quot;Warriors are, and will remain, the best tanks in the game. They are, and always have been, one of the least versatile classes in the game. Get used to it if you want to play a warrior. &quot;<br>
<br>
let me point out the versatile section. yes we are the least versatile, it is because we should be far and away the best at melee tanking BECAUSE ITS ALL WE DO. (that was not shouting, that was emphasis).<br>
<br>
before all this AA mumbo jumbo, and this supposed &quot;class balancing&quot;. we fit this description. we stand there and get hit, and deliver hits, we hit taunt to give us that extra bit of aggro to keep the mob standing in front of us. we did not deliver as much damage as a monk or as a rogue because, while they are pure melee classes, but they are tweaked/pointed into more of an offensive melee rather then a defensive one, like us warriors.  Pallies/SK's were classes that traded some of that offensive power and tanking ability to develop the arcane/diving magics. This gave them some utility and versatility. They were no where near the equal of a Warrior in combat, they would have to use those spells to compensate for this. Warriors are defined from each other at this time ONLY by thier gear. this was reflected in the game by the Warr only gear having that extra 10-15% AC compared to the pally/sk items. here are the kunark BPs for example (12.5% better AC with kunark armors)<br>
<br>
War=Cobalt Breastplate  +45 AC +12 Str +12 Sta +12 Dex +50 HP +20.00 Wt  <br>
SK=Blood Ember Breastplate  +40 AC +12 Str +8 Sta +8 Agi +8 Dex +10.00 Wt   <br>
Pal=Deepwater Breastplate  +40 AC +10 Str +10 Agi +10 Wis +50 Mana +10.00 Wt  <br>
<br>
don't forget that this was when you were lucky to have a 1200 AC, much less talking about AC softcaps.<br>
<br>
now, assuming that you do have all your AA filled in, you once again find that the only thing that defines a tank is his gear.(no, i doubt such a mythic being exists at this time, but if wer'e talking balance let's take it to the extreme as that's where the differences will be best seen). the same 10 BP's show up under each under a search (using ACx10, hpx1) for pally, sk and warrior. so this means that pallies, SK's and Warriors can now all have the same AC. <br>
<br>
Great Shadow Platemail <br>
,Heavy Yttrium Chestplate<br>
Breastplate of the Void  <br>
Breastplate of Speed  <br>
Breastplate of Eradication  <br>
Chestplate of Fiery Might  <br>
True Mithril Breastplate  <br>
Breastplate of Superiority  <br>
Jenniy's Two-tone Cuirass  <br>
Warmaster's Ribcage <br>
<br>
so basically, in the armor category, pallies and SK's are now the same as warriors.<br>
<br>
now onto offense..no matter what  weapon your wielding, its what offensive category/bracket your in that defines just how much you can do offensivly. and from the oct 8 patch, we get the biggest of the &quot;balancing changes&quot;.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Paladins and Shadowknights, besides the benefits they gain from the two-handed weapons change mentioned above, have also been moved to the same combat tables as warriors. In the future we intend to examine the existing one-handed weapons useable by knights for possible upgrades. We are also increasing the Taunt skill cap for these two classes to 220.&quot;<br>
<br>
it was this patch that raised warriors taunt cap to 230. this was to make up for the extra damage that every other melee started doing. but basically, we went from &quot;kings of offense&quot; to being the same as the pallies and SK's..you know, those guys who GAVE UP some offensive power to cast spells.<br>
<br>
so in summary for ya'll that might not have followed this...<br>
<br>
1)warriors were the king of battle, we had a better melee bracket, we had better armor. pallies/sk's had lesser armor and lesser melee to compensate for thier use of spells.<br>
<br>
2) oct 8 patch rolls in, pallies and sk's are moved to the same melee bracket as warriors. all 3 have taunt increased, warriors get an extra 5% taunt over pallies and sk's because now all the other classes that swing a sword make more tuant. but basically TANKS LOOSE &quot;THE KING OF BATTLE&quot; title and now share offensive power with the pallies/SK's.<br>
<br>
3) with luclin, and velious armor went away from class specific's towards eveyrone having a chance at them. this took away the AC/HP advantage that warriors had over pallies/sk's. this is the straw that made pallies and SK's viable tanks.<br>
<br>
so, when we gave up the ability to cast spells, or backstab, or deal out damage to be the king of battle in the earliest of &quot;game concepts&quot;, pallies/sk's sacraficed this martial ability by learning spells, and ti made sense. now they get everything a tank does, AND get thier spells too.<br>
<br>
that's what this whole post started as. warriors have no job, we have been replaces by sk's and pallies in all but 1% of end mobs. this is what we are asking verant to take a look at if they ever read this board.<br>
<br>
or did i miss something? take care, and remember caps are for emphasis, not yelling.<br>
<br>
have a nice day.<br>
<br>
<br>
3) luclin comes out,<br>
<br>
<br>
